cohortDefinitions.logicDescription:
Status: Pending peer review.
hashTag: #PhenotypePhebruary2023
Contributor: Maxim Moinat
Forum: https://forums.ohdsi.org/t/phenotype-phebruary-2023-p11-neurofibromatosis-type-1-with-optical-pathway-glioma/18236
Logic: Persons with an optic nerve glioma OR non-malignant neoplasm of optic nerve (‘Optic nerve glioma of orbit’, ‘Neoplasm of optic nerve and sheath’, ‘Benign neoplasm of optic nerve’), and a diagnosis of neurofibromatosis anytime in persons history.The code for neoplasm of optic nerve is in a separate branch of SNOMED.
cohortDefinitions.name: [PPheb2023] Optical pathway glioma or non malignant neoplasm of optic nerve w neurofibromatosis (FP)

cohortDefinitions.logicDescription:
Status: Pending peer review.

Contributor: Maxim Moinat
Forum: https://forums.ohdsi.org/t/phenotype-phebruary-2023-p11-neurofibromatosis-type-1-with-optical-pathway-glioma/18236
Logic: Persons with diagnosis of NF1 diagnosis code (SNOMED:92824003) or descendants (genetic mutation, freckling, elephantiasis, spinal NF, caf-au-lait macules, neurofibromas, Noonan syndrome, segmental NF1).These codes are the preferred granular coding for NF1.
